/li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"IAMPRAutomationWorkflowCompleteSystemDocumentation-Troubleshootin=
g">Troubleshooting</h2>
<h3 id=3D"IAMPRAutomationWorkflowCompleteSystemDocumentation-CommonIssues">=
Common Issues</h3>
<h4 id=3D"IAMPRAutomationWorkflowCompleteSystemDocumentation-Issue1:PRNotDe=
tected">Issue 1: PR Not Detected</h4>
<p><strong>Symptoms</strong>: PR created but no Teams notification after 5 =
minutes</p>
<p><strong>Possible Causes</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>PR Poller Lambda not running</li>
<li>Repository not in config.json</li>
<li>GitHub API rate limiting</li>
<li>VPC connectivity issues</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Diagnosis</strong>:</p>
<pre><code class=3D"language-bash"># Check PR Poller logs
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/gts-github-pr-poll-poller-dev --follow

# Check EventBridge rule
aws events describe-rule --name github-pr-polling-dev

# Check DynamoDB for PR
aws dynamodb get-item \
  --table-name github-open-prs-dev \
  --key '{"repo_pr": {"S": "Centralized-IAM-Accounts/idc-gts-roles-prod#250=
"}}'
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Solutions</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Verify EventBridge rule is enabled</li>
<li>Add repository to config.json if missing</li>
<li>Check GitHub API rate limits in logs</li>
<li>Verify VPC security groups allow GitHub Enterprise access</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h4 id=3D"IAMPRAutomationWorkflowCompleteSystemDocumentation-Issue2:Workflo=
wNotStarting">Issue 2: Workflow Not Starting</h4>
<p><strong>Symptoms</strong>: PR in DynamoDB but execution_status not set</=
p>
<p><strong>Possible Causes</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Step Function Trigger Lambda not subscribed to stream</li>
<li>DynamoDB Stream disabled</li>
<li>IAM permissions missing</li>
<li>Step Function execution limit reached</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Diagnosis</strong>:</p>
<pre><code class=3D"language-bash"># Check Step Function Trigger logs
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/gts-github-pr-poll-stepfunction-trigger-dev --fol=
low

# Check DynamoDB Stream
aws dynamodb describe-table --table-name github-open-prs-dev \
  | jq '.Table.StreamSpecification'

# Check event source mapping
aws lambda list-event-source-mappings \
  --function-name gts-github-pr-poll-stepfunction-trigger-dev
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Solutions</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Verify event source mapping is enabled</li>
<li>Enable DynamoDB Stream if disabled</li>
<li>Check IAM role has states:StartExecution permission</li>
<li>Check Step Function execution limits in AWS Console</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h4 id=3D"IAMPRAutomationWorkflowCompleteSystemDocumentation-Issue3:Validat=
ionChecksFailing">Issue 3: Validation Checks Failing</h4>
<p><strong>Symptoms</strong>: All PRs showing FAILED status</p>
<p><strong>Possible Causes</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Validation Lambda errors</li>
<li>GitHub API access issues</li>
<li>Invalid validation logic</li>
<li>Missing IAM policies in PRs</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Diagnosis</strong>:</p>
<pre><code class=3D"language-bash"># Check Security Scan logs
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/gts-github-pr-poll-security-scan-dev --follow

# Check Compliance Check logs
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/gts-github-pr-poll-compliance-check-dev --follow

# Check IAM Boundary Checker logs
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/gts-github-pr-poll-iam-boundary-checker-dev --fol=
low
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Solutions</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Review Lambda error logs for specific issues</li>
<li>Verify GitHub token has correct permissions</li>
<li>Review validation logic for false negatives</li>
<li>Verify PRs contain IAM policy files</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h4 id=3D"IAMPRAutomationWorkflowCompleteSystemDocumentation-Issue4:TeamsNo=
tificationsNotSent">Issue 4: Teams Notifications Not Sent</h4>
<p><strong>Symptoms</strong>: Workflow completes but no Teams notification<=
/p>
<p><strong>Possible Causes</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Teams Notifier Lambda not subscribed to stream</li>
<li>Teams webhook URL invalid</li>
<li>execution_status not set to COMPLETED</li>
<li>final_status missing</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Diagnosis</strong>:</p>
<pre><code class=3D"language-bash"># Check Teams Notifier logs
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/gts-github-pr-poll-notifier-dev --follow

# Check DynamoDB record
aws dynamodb get-item \
  --table-name github-open-prs-dev \
  --key '{"repo_pr": {"S": "Centralized-IAM-Accounts/idc-gts-roles-prod#250=
"}}' \
  | jq '.Item.execution_status, .Item.final_status'

# Test Teams webhook
curl -X POST &lt;teams_webhook_url&gt; \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"text": "Test notification"}'
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Solutions</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Verify event source mapping filter: <code>execution_status =3D "COMPLET=
ED"</code></li>
<li>Verify Teams webhook URL in Secrets Manager</li>
<li>Check Step Function completed successfully</li>
<li>Verify final_status was set by Final Status Checker</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h4 id=3D"IAMPRAutomationWorkflowCompleteSystemDocumentation-Issue5:Regress=
ionTestsNotRunning">Issue 5: Regression Tests Not Running</h4>
<p><strong>Symptoms</strong>: Historical PR Fetcher invoked but no test res=
ults</p>
<p><strong>Possible Causes</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>S3 cache empty</li>
<li>Sampling parameters too restrictive</li>
<li>Regression table not receiving INSERTs</li>
<li>Regression Step Function not starting</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Diagnosis</strong>:</p>
<pre><code class=3D"language-bash"># Check Historical PR Fetcher logs
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/gts-github-pr-poll-historical-pr-fetcher-dev --fo=
llow

# Check S3 cache
aws s3 ls s3://iam-automation-historical-prs-dev/ --recursive

# Check regression table
aws dynamodb scan --table-name github-prs-regression-test-dev \
  --limit 10

# Check regression Step Function
aws stepfunctions list-executions \
  --state-machine-arn &lt;regression-stepfunction-arn&gt; \
  --max-results 10
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Solutions</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Run incremental_update mode to populate S3 cache</li>
<li>Adjust sampling parameters (increase max_prs)</li>
<li>Verify Historical PR Fetcher has DynamoDB PutItem permission</li>
<li>Check regression Step Function Trigger Lambda logs</li>
</ol>
